AIM:  b. Write a program to develop a small website with multiple routes using Express. Js

Description:
This Express app supports multiple routes:
•	/ → Home Page
•	/about → About Page
•	/contact → Contact Page

Procedure:
1.	Set up a Node project and install Express (as in Program a).
2.	Create an app.js file.
3.	Define multiple routes like /, /about, and /contact.
4.	Use res.send() or res.sendFile() to return responses.
5.	Run the server and open different routes in the browser

Program:

const express = require('express');
const app = express();
const port = 3000;

app.get('/', (req, res) => res.send('Home Page'));
app.get('/about', (req, res) => res.send('About Page'));
app.get('/contact', (req, res) => res.send('Contact Page'));

app.listen(port, () => {
  console.log(Website running at http://localhost:${port});
});

Output:

Output in Browser:
•	http://localhost:3000/ → Home Page
•	http://localhost:3000/about → About Page
•	http://localhost:3000/contact → Contact Page
